p:
The digestive enzymes (amylase, lipase, and protease) activities were determined in the ileal digesta of quails at the end of the experimental period (1 bird per replicate). The quail ileum from Meckel's diverticulum to 2 cm above the junction of ileocecal region was dissected, and the ileal contents were aseptically collected in screw-capped sterile specimen vials. Activities of amylase, lipase and protease were determined in the digestive samples according to the procedure of 
 Najafi et al. (2005; 
 2006).
